  "model": "eleven_v3",
  "text": "A new census counts nine thousand export factories that closed this year. Automation and American tariffs both show up tangled together in the numbers. Local officials want the report buried before the plenary session convenes. Workers from three of the largest closures are already petitioning the labor bureau.",
